OSOGBO – Governor Adegboyega Oye­tola of the State of Osun has congratulated Christians in the State and across the coun­try for witnessing yet another Christmas celebration. He also urged Nigerians to embrace love, tolerance, gen­erosity and peaceful co-exis­tence which Jesus Christ stood for. The governor added, “Let me reiterate that all youth car­nivals, the countdown to New Year ceremonies are banned.” EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The governor in a state­ment by his Chief Press Secre­tary, Ismail Omipidan said the celebration offered Nigerians the opportunity to reflect on God’s love and compassion for man as epitomised in the gift of Christ to the world. Oyetola, who particular­ly enjoined Christians in the State of Osun to use the Christmas period to reflect on their relationship with one another and show love to their neighbours also urged the people to shun religious sen­timents by working together for the progress of the State. Bishop Of Awka Charges FG On Diversification Yuletide: Gov. Ugwuanyi Prays For Divine Intervention This was just as he called on Osun residents and citi­zens in particular and Nige­rians, in general, to ensure that all celebrations are done in moderation and in adherence to all COVID-19 protocols to limit the spread of the disease. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION